Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` ≈ iOS `WillResignActive` (lost focus, may still be visible)
- Android `OnStop` ≈ iOS `DidEnterBackground` (fully backgrounded)
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback signatures, override `OnStopped()` on a `Window` subclass — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically:

```csharp
public class AppWindow : Window
{
    public AppWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    protected override void OnStopped()
    {
        base.OnStopped();
        // Runs on both platforms when app is backgrounded
    }
}
```

Return it from `App.CreateWindow`:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
    => new AppWindow(new AppShell());
```
